    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">People</h2>
          <p><a href="https://github.blog/2020-04-14-sawfish-phishing-campaign-targets-github-users/">Sawfish phishing campaign targets GitHub users</a><br />
            &ldquo;Over the last week, GitHub has received reports related to a phishing campaign targeting our customers. We&rsquo;re publishing this blog to increase awareness of this ongoing threat.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://devops.com/devops-chats-devsecops-and-openshift-with-red-hat/">DevOps Chats: DevSecOps and OpenShift, with Red Hat</a><br />
            When Kirsten Newcomer speaks, I listen. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re seeing that shift left a lot, but then there&rsquo;s all these other range of things that you should be doing and can be doing to build security into the platform. And so, when we saw pod security policies in Kubernetes, for example, that&rsquo;s a way that the Kube admin can take advantage of the Linux features that enable container isolation at the Kubernetes layer and enforce things like ensure that a container doesn&rsquo;t run with unnecessary privileges.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://nora.codes/post/stop-making-students-use-eclipse/">Stop Making Students Use Eclipse</a><br />
            &ldquo;When students don&rsquo;t understand what a file is, or haven&rsquo;t ever edited text in anything but Microsoft Word and don&rsquo;t realize they can edit code outside of an IDE, they will not be able to do the crucial work of self-directed learning that is a hallmark of all computer science success.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://hbr.org/2020/04/how-working-parents-can-support-one-another">How Working Parents Can Support One Another</a><br />
            I know there are thousands of working parents juggling kids right now. Yes, Max is around most of the day, but we&rsquo;re fortunate in that we&rsquo;re a single-income household. If you&rsquo;re working with folks that are tagging out of meetings and directly into parenting so their partner can do their meeting, please give them the advantage of every ounce of flexibility you have.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/jpl/nasas-curiosity-keeps-rolling-as-team-operates-rover-from-home">NASA&rsquo;s Curiosity Keeps Rolling As Team Operates Rover From Home</a><br />
            If these folks can control a rover on another fucking planet while working from home, what&rsquo;s your organization&rsquo;s excuse? I&rsquo;ve talked to four different doctors the past couple weeks and every, single one of them thinks we might have changed medicine forever at this point.</p>

          <p><a href="https://hbr.org/2020/04/is-it-even-possible-to-focus-on-anything-right-now">Is It Even Possible to Focus on Anything Right Now?</a><br />
            It&rsquo;s not. Stop acting like we&rsquo;re all okay.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
