    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">Tools</h2>
          <p><a href="https://developers.redhat.com/blog/2020/04/15/crafting-kubernetes-operators/">Crafting Kubernetes Operators</a><br />
            &ldquo;In this talk, you&rsquo;ll learn about crafting Kubernetes Operators from Josh Wood and Burr Sutter.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&amp;px=Git-Newline-Leak-Vulnerability">Git Releases Security Update With Newline Character Creating Possible Credential Leak</a><br />
            &ldquo;A member of Google&rsquo;s Project Zero team discovered that a specially crafted URL could trick the Git client into sending credential information for an alternative host to an attacker&rsquo;s host.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://devopsi.sh/gke-aks-e3ad2">EKS vs. GKE vs. AKS - Comparing the top three cloud providers</a><br />
            Not all managed Kubernetes services are created the same. They support different features and options for their cluster control planes and nodes, and they vary in how much management they really provide. To help cut through the fog, StackRox performed a hands-on, side-by-side comparison of the top three services (EKS, AKS, GKE) to help you understand their current state and trade-offs - updated April 2020 <em>SPONSORED</em></p>

          <p><a href="https://thenewstack.io/opentelemetry-steps-up-to-manage-the-mayhem-of-microservices/">OpenTelemetry Steps up to Manage the Mayhem of Microservices</a><br />
            &ldquo;Work continues to make OpenTelemetry the standard set of vendor-neutral specifications and associated tools for capturing cloud native operational data.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://gumroad.com/l/aws-good-parts">The Good Parts of AWS</a><br />
            I bought this book to read after I finish The Unicorn Project (finally).</p>

          <p><a href="https://blog.christophersmart.com/2020/04/11/fedora-silverblue-is-an-amazing-immutable-desktop/">Fedora Silverblue is an amazing immutable desktop</a><br />
            Layers aren&rsquo;t just for containers.</p>

          <p><a href="https://devopsi.sh/aws-lambda-97890">Online Debug for AWS Lambda on your IDE!</a><br />
            Thundra allows you to natively debug your serverless applications on the cloud with their own permissions. Thundra&rsquo;s online-debugger sets up a secure bridge between your AWS Lambda environment and your IDE. VSCode and IntelliJ IDEA are natively supported with plugins. For other IDEs, we provide a portable client to foster the integration with any IDEs. Start debugging Node.js, Python and Java functions for free today! <em>SPONSORED</em></p>

          <p><a href="https://github.com/alexellis/awesome-baremetal">alexellis/awesome-baremetal</a><br />
            &ldquo;Bare-metal is awesome. Let&rsquo;s share our favourite tools.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://github.com/raphamorim/lucario">raphamorim/lucario</a><br />
            &ldquo;The best flat theme for Vim, Atom, Sublime Text, Jetbrains Editors, Terminal.app, iTerm, Xcode and XTerm&rdquo; I switched to this theme in VSCode while writing this newsletter. I had to turn the brightness down on my monitor, that&rsquo;s probably a good thing. So far, I like it.</p>
        </mj-text>
